parameters: Clea: Is it inside that building?

Mage Relm: P-Please look at this instead! An enormous number
of books! Can I take them home!?

Hmm... That would be troublesome... It's a valuable
collection.

Male Bibliophile: It's a lamentable era when a delicate
young girl like you is treated with hostility when she
returns home, being mistaken for a robber...
Thief Nora: I-It's not robbery, it's thievery!

Male Bibliophile: Isn't it even worse... Did you steal the
crystal from the bar owner?
Male Bibliophile: Is it alright... to bring it to my house?

Priestess Sophia: Actually, I've been following in the
footsteps of the hero-sama--

Male Bibliophile: What is it, what is it, what is it! Are
you also here? Hurry up and tell me!

Male Bibliophile: The mages of Kanonas may have knowledge,
but they lack romance!

Male Bibliophile: I have been chasing after the hero as a
human for many years!

Male Bibliophile: This is a painting called 'The Beginning'.
In the center, there is an abstract depiction of a hero,
with sisters painted on the left and right.

Priestess Sophia: The legend of the sisters... the people
who became the motif for the sisters' statue at the Kasaro
bathhouse.

Male Bibliophile: I considered this legend to be an actual
event, compared to other hero legends that were more flashy.

Male Bibliophile: I found it there! The name of the young
man who was called a hero... I, me, myself...

Male Bibliophile: I'll prepare dinner. Tomorrow we'll go to
war, it's the master's fault. Let's take the dog for a walk.
I spilled wine, I killed someone.

Tableau of Memories: Fig Tart, Sunlight Filtering Through
Trees, Children Holding Hands with a Wounded Kitten, White
Light, Sun on Earth, Hero

Mage Relm: Memories are gathering... I-I don't know, but
it's definitely going to be troublesome!

Clea: If something is gathering, let's defeat it before we
can shake it off.
Clea: ...It seems like it finally disappeared.

Mage Relm: I'm reading the diary that was dropped... but
some of the characters and words are no longer used in
modern times, it seems.
Mage Relm: Please give me a little time.
Clea: What is this 'Legend of the Sisters' all about?

Thief Nora: I'm curious too! It's about the statue of the
sisters that was at the Kasaro Bathhouse, right?
Priestess Sophia: Well, it's a very simple story, but--

Mage Relm: I understand, I understand! I was able to
decipher the diary and discover the name of the hero!

Mage Relm: It seems like I found it from the stone tablet
that is believed to be the birthplace of the sisters. Now,
let's surprise everyone with this significant achievement!
